  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Retinopathy of prematurity (ROP) is one of the major morbidity among preterm infants.
      Although, local anesthetics reduce pain to some extent, eye examination still remains as a
      painful procedure. The investigators aimed to evaluate the effect of oral paracetamol
      combined with local anesthetics for pain relief during ophthalmological examination.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
